South African Monthly Budget Deficit $3.7 Billion in April, Treasury Says

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-05-31T05:37:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/south-african-monthly-budget-deficit-3-7-billion-in-april-treasury-says.html
South Africa  posted a budget deficit
of 25.6 billion rand ($3.7 billion) in April, compared with
deficit of 25.1 billion rand in the same month a year ago, the
National Treasury said.  Tax revenue was little changed at 37 billion rand, while
expenditure increased 0.7 percent to 62.6 billion rand, the
Pretoria-based Treasury said on its website today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  